  m_Name: External_abdominal_oblique_muscle.L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: External_abdominal_oblique_muscle.L
  partName: External abdominal oblique muscle Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left external abdominal oblique muscle is a broad superficial muscle covering
    the lateral abdominal wall of the canine body. Originating from the ribs and
    thoracolumbar fascia, it inserts onto the abdominal midline and pelvic structures.
    This muscle supports trunk movement by assisting in spinal flexion, lateral bending,
    and rotation during locomotion.
  - It also plays an important role in abdominal compression, helping support internal
    organs and contributing to breathing mechanics during forceful respiration. Coordinated
    contractions stabilize the trunk and improve balance during movement and posture
    changes.
